(40, 12, 18, 23, 42, 1, 1, 'my servant, whom I have chosen', 'Servant and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the figure of ''my servant'' who is chosen and beloved. They also share the theme of bringing forth ''judgment to the Gentiles,'' highlighting a prophetic connection between the two texts.', 'prophecy', 0.622, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
